  "text": "The protocol used here has been described elsewhere [CITATION_1] . Briefly, the slides with human tissue sections were rehydrated and washed in PBS containing 136 mM NaCl, 2.7 mM KCl, 10 mM Na 2 HPO 4 , and 1.8 mM KH 2 PO 4 , pH 7.4. Endogenous peroxidase was quenched by incubation for 15 min in 1% H 2 O 2 in 100% methanol; slides were rinsed twice in PBS and treated with proteinase K (20 mg/ml; Roche Diagnostics) in 50 mM Tris-HCL and 5 mM EDTA (pH 8.0) for 10 min at 37C. Acetylation was performed by incubation in 0.1 M triethanolamine (pH 8.0) with 0.25% acetic anhydride for 10 min at room temperature. After washes in PBS, tissues were dehydrated in graded series of ethanol (50%, 70%, 80%, 95%, and 100%) and air-dried. Hybridization was carried out using an hybridization buffer [50% deionized formamide, 20 mM Tris-HCl (pH 8.0), 0.3 M NaCl, 5 mM EDTA (pH 8.0), 10% dextran sulfate, 13 Denhardt solution, 0.5 mg/ml tRNA (Roche Diagnostics), 0.2 mg/ml salmon sperm DNA, 200 mM dithiothreitol, and 0.5 mg/ml DIG-labeled probe]. Before applying to the tissue, the hybridization cocktail was denatured for 2 min at 95C. Slides were incubated overnight at 50C in a humidified chamber.",
